                                        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                                        <h3>How much does it cost to hire an app development company in the USA in 2026?</h3>
                                        <p>US boutique agencies charge $80k-$220k for a typical MVP and $300k-$1.2M for enterprise scope. The same scope built by a top-15% Indian partner runs $25k-$70k. The cost gap is labour arbitrage; quality at the top tier is comparable.</p>
                                        <h3>Are Indian app development companies as good as US ones?</h3>
                                        <p>The top 15% in India - studios shipping for Y Combinator, Sequoia and Series-B clients - match US senior-engineer quality on architecture, code review and testing. The bottom 60% (freelancer marketplaces, body-shops) do not. Vet engineers, not agency logos.</p>
                                        <h3>How do I protect my IP when working with an Indian agency?</h3>
                                        <p>Sign a work-for-hire agreement, take ownership of the GitHub org, get NDAs from each contributing engineer, and run weekly source-code transfers. Top-tier studios will agree to all four without negotiation.</p>
                                        <h3>Will time-zone overlap be a problem?</h3>
                                        <p>Indian morning (9am-1pm IST) overlaps with US evening (11:30pm-3:30am EST). Indian evening (5pm-9pm IST) overlaps with US morning (7:30am-11:30am EST). Most engagements run a daily 9pm IST / 11:30am EST standup; works for everyone.</p>
                                        <h3>How fast can a project start with an Indian partner?</h3>
                                        <p>Top studios start within 5-10 business days of contract signature. We typically complete discovery in week 1, ship Sprint 1 deliverables in week 3, and have a usable beta in 6-8 weeks for MVP scope.</p>
